ort, addressing psychosocial needs, and facilitating access to community resources.</li></ul><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-1373_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><strong>Compliance with regulations</strong></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eGPXGI hfOvrX pf-1375_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-1376_ pf-text-1">Social care providers must adhere to relevant legislation and regulations, ensuring that policies and procedures align with the Care Act 2014, Health and Social Care Act 2008, and CQC standards.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-1378_ pf-text-1">Regular training and updates are essential to maintain compliance and deliver high-quality care that meets regulatory requirements.</li></ul><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-1380_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><strong>Promoting self-management</strong></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eGPXGI hfOvrX pf-1382_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-1383_ pf-text-1">Empowering individuals to self-manage their long-term conditions is critical to promoting independence and improving health outcomes.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-1385_ pf-text-1">Through education, support, and encouragement, social care professionals can help individuals develop self-management skills and confidence in managing their health.</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-jrQzAO jIEVBe pf-1387_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6">