ges. Social care providers can make a profound difference in the lives of those they serve by prioritising person-centred care, addressing holistic needs, and staying abreast of regulations and best practices.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-c914" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-XxNYO gsQFwr pf-1412_ pf-color-scheme-1 pf-lg-hide pf-md-hide pf-sm-hide"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-dkYRCH hYpqjU"><div class="sc-jrQzAO jIEVBe pf-1413_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-1414_"><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-1415_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">In social care in the UK, managing long-term conditions is not just a duty but a profound responsibility that directly impacts the lives of countless individuals. From chronic illnesses like diabetes and heart disease to conditions such as dementia and Parkinson's disease, the effective management of long-term conditions is paramount to ensuring the well-being, independence, and dignity of those in need.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-jrQzAO jIEVBe pf-1417_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-1418_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hmjpVf IvCUC pf-1419_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key facts and statistics</h3><div class="sc-jrQzAO jIEVBe pf-1421_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-1422_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Navigating_Legislation_ComplyPlus_for_Children_s_Home_Regulations_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1710431109" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Navigating_Legislation_ComplyPlus_for_Children_s_Home_Regulations_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1710431109 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Navigating_Legislation_ComplyPlus_for_Children_s_Home_Regulations_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1500x.jpg?v=1710431109 1280w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Navigating_Legislation_ComplyPlus_for_Children_s_Home_Regulations_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1000x.jpg?v=1710431109 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Navigating_Legislation_ComplyPlus_for_Children_s_Home_Regulations_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1710431109 320w" width="1612" height="1228" alt="Mastering Managing Long-term Conditions: Social Care Management Strategies - ComplyPlus LMS™ - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Mastering Managing Long-term Conditions: Social Care Management Strategies - ComplyPlus LMS™ - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jQrDum jseZXh pf-1423_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-1424_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by  Rawpixel via Envato Elements</p></div></div></div><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eGPXGI hfOvrX pf-1426_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-1427_ pf-text-1">According to the Office for National Statistics, around 15 million people in the UK are living with a long-term health condition, representing nearly a quarter of the population.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-1429_ pf-text-1">Long-term conditions are estimated to account for 70% of England's total health and social care expenditure, highlighting the significant financial burden they place on the healthcare system.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-1431_ pf-text-1">Research published in the British Medical Journal suggests that effective management of long-term conditions can lead to a 30-50% reduction in hospital admissions and emergency department visits.</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-jrQzAO jIEVBe pf-1433_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-1434_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hmjpVf IvCUC pf-1435_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions</h3><div class="sc-jrQzAO jIEVBe pf-1437_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-1438_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Comprehensive_Chronic_Health_Conditions_Support_Long-term_Health_Condition_Care_-_ComplyPlus_LMS_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1713281391" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Comprehensive_Chronic_Health_Conditions_Support_Long-term_Health_Condition_Care_-_ComplyPlus_LMS_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1713281391 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Comprehensive_Chronic_Health_Conditions_Support_Long-term_Health_Condition_Care_-_ComplyPlus_LMS_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1000x.jpg?v=1713281391 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Comprehensive_Chronic_Health_Conditions_Support_Long-term_Health_Condition_Care_-_ComplyPlus_LMS_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1713281391 320w" width="1000" height="667" alt="Comprehensive Chronic Health Conditions Support Long-term Health Condition Care - ComplyPlus LMS™ - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Comprehensive Chronic Health Conditions Support Long-term Health Condition Care - ComplyPlus LMS™ - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jQrDum jseZXh pf-1439_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-1440_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by seventyfourimages via Envato Elements</p></div></div></div><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-1442_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><strong>Managing long-term conditions (social care)</strong> - The coordinated provision of support and services to enhance the quality of life and independence of individuals living with chronic health conditions within social care settings.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-jrQzAO jIEVBe pf-1444_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-1445_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hmjpVf IvCUC pf-1446_ pf-heading-1-h3">Relevant legislation, regulations, and best practices</h3><div class="sc-jrQzAO jIEVBe pf-1448_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-1449_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Empowering_Person-centred_Care_Planning_Symptom_Management_Strategies_-_ComplyPlus_LMS_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1713281528" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Empowering_Person-centred_Care_Planning_Symptom_Management_Strategies_-_ComplyPlus_LMS_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1713281528 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Empowering_Person-centred_Care_Planning_Symptom_Management_Strategies_-_ComplyPlus_LMS_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1000x.jpg?v=1713281528 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Empowering_Person-centred_Care_Planning_Symptom_Management_Strategies_-_ComplyPlus_LMS_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1713281528 320w" width="1000" height="667" alt="Empowering Person-centred Care Planning Symptom Management Strategies - ComplyPlus LMS™ - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Empowering Person-centred Care Planning Symptom Management Strategies - ComplyPlus LMS™ - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jQrDum jseZXh pf-1450_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-1451_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by LightFieldStudios&nbsp;via Envato Elements</p></div></div></div><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eGPXGI hfOvrX pf-1453_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-1454_ pf-text-1"><strong>The Care Act 2014</strong> - provides a legal framework for social care in England, emphasising person-centred care planning, safeguarding, and promoting well-being for individuals with long-term conditions.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-1456_ pf-text-1"><strong>Health and Social Care Act 2008</strong> - This Act Sets out regulations and standards for healthcare and social care services, ensuring quality and safety in managing long-term conditions.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-1458_ pf-text-1"><strong>National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) Guidelines</strong> - Offers evidence-based guidance on best practices for managing specific long-term conditions, informing decision-making and care provision.</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-jrQzAO jIEVBe pf-1460_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-1461_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hmjpVf IvCUC pf-1462_ pf-heading-1-h3">Empowering excellence - Managing long-term conditions (social care) strategies</h3><div class="sc-jrQzAO jIEVBe pf-1464_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-1465_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Expertise_in_Care_for_Chronic_Illnesses_Dementia_Care_and_Support_-_ComplyPlus_LMS_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1713281676" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Expertise_in_Care_for_Chronic_Illnesses_Dementia_Care_and_Support_-_ComplyPlus_LMS_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1713281676 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Expertise_in_Care_for_Chronic_Illnesses_Dementia_Care_and_Support_-_ComplyPlus_LMS_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1000x.jpg?v=1713281676 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Expertise_in_Care_for_Chronic_Illnesses_Dementia_Care_and_Support_-_ComplyPlus_LMS_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1713281676 320w" width="1000" height="1500" alt="Expertise in Care for Chronic Illnesses Dementia Care and Support - ComplyPlus LMS™ - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Expertise in Care for Chronic Illnesses Dementia Care and Support - ComplyPlus LMS™ - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jQrDum jseZXh pf-1466_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-1467_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by  monkeybusiness

 via Envato Elements</p></div></div></div><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-1469_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><strong>Importance of person-centred care</strong></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eGPXGI hfOvrX pf-1471_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-1472_ pf-text-1">Person-centred care, which recognises the individual's preferences, values, and goals, is at the heart of effective management of long-term conditions.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-1474_ pf-text-1">Person-centred care promotes autonomy and enhances satisfaction with care received by involving individuals in decision-making and tailoring care plans to their unique needs.</li></ul><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-1476_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><strong>Addressing holistic needs</strong></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eGPXGI hfOvrX pf-1478_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-1479_ pf-text-1">Effective management of long-term conditions requires a holistic approach that considers not only physical health but also the emotional, social, and spiritual well-being of individuals.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-1481_ pf-text-1">Social care professionals are crucial in providing comprehensive support, addressing psychosocial needs, and facilitating access to community resources.</li></ul><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-1483_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><strong>Compliance with regulations</strong></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;-